(8, 'SYLHET', 'AL leader chopped dead in Sylhet ', 'Miscreants chopped a union level leader of ruling Awami League (AL) and injured another at Charkhai union under Biyanibazar upazila of the district on Wednesday afternoon (June 22). - See more at: http://www.en.sylhetview24.com/news/details/sylhet/324#sthash.7BnFBnJn.dpuf\r\n               ', 'Miscreants chopped a union level leader of ruling Awami League (AL) and injured another at Charkhai union under Biyanibazar upazila of the district on Wednesday afternoon (June 22).\r\n\r\nThe deceased was identified as Mahtab Uddin, 35, agriculture affairs secretary at Charkhai union, hailed from the village.\r\n\r\nLocals said the murdered was the consequence of clashes over land property.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, police detained eight from the spot regarding the incident.\r\n\r\nWitnesses said a gang of 10/12 miscreants chopped Mahtab Uddin dead in broad daylight while he was returning home on a bullock cart.\r\n\r\nBiyanibazar Thana officer-in-charge (OC) Juber Ahmed confirmed the matter.\r\n\r\nHe further said the injured was taken to MAG Osmani Medical College Hospital. \r\n               ', '324.jpeg'),
(10, 'SYLHET', 'One held with VOIP sets, gun powder in Sylhet ', 'The police arrested a youth and seized five machines of voice over internet protocol, laptops, chocolate bombs and gun powder from him in Sylhet on Friday afternoon.\r\n               ', 'The police arrested a youth and seized five machines of voice over internet protocol, laptops, chocolate bombs and gun powder from him in Sylhet on Friday afternoon.\r\n\r\nThe arrested was identified as Sajib Hasan, 22, residence of Purba Pir Mahalla in Sylhet city.\r\n\r\nLocal people said Sajib and his two friends were living in a flat of Group View Tower in the area for the last three months and their neighbours became suspicious of them as they hardly went out of their flat.\r\n\r\nFarhad Chowdhury Shamim, councilor of the ward no. 6 of the Sylhet City Corporation, told that they went to Sajibâ€™s house at about 11:00am.\r\n\r\nHowever, his friends left the house after seeing them, Shamim said.\r\n\r\nLater, Biman Bandar police visited the spot and arrested Sajib along with five VOIP machines, two laptops, a Grameenphone modem, several SIMs, five chocolate bombs and gun powder, he added.\r\n\r\nBiman Bandar police officer-in-charge Gausul Hossain said Sajib confessed that he was a VOIP technician.\r\n\r\nA case was filed, the OC said, adding that they were trying arrest the other two.\r\n               ', '266.jpeg'),
(11, 'SYLHET', 'School boy killed in lightning in Sylhet ', 'A school student was killed by struck in lightning in Sylhet on Monday morning.\r\n               ', ' A school student was killed by struck in lightning in Sylhet on Monday morning.\r\n\r\nThe deceased was identified as Nayeem Ahmad, 16, a class ten student of Ichhamati High school at Jakiganj upazila in the district and son of Machhan Miah of Topkhana village at Manikpur union of the same upazila, police said.\r\n\r\nLocal sources said that a thunderbolt stuck on Nayeem at around 8-00 am when he was working in a paddy field near his home in the Topkhana village living him critically injured.\r\n\r\nThe victim was died on his way to the Jakiganj upazila health complex, the sources said.\r\n\r\nWhen contacted, Jakiganj police officer-in-charge Safiqur Rahman confirmed  of the lightning and said the victimâ€™s body was handed over to the relatives after preparing a report of spot examination.\r\n               ', 'demo.jpg'),
(12, 'SYLHET', 'Sylhet BCL leader arrested for attacking on CPB-BSD rally', 'A court in Sylhet on Monday ordered to send the former acting vice-president of the district unit of Bangladesh Chhatra League, Hiran Mahmud Nipu, to jail in the case for attacking on a joint-rally of Communist Party of Bangladesh and Bangladesh Samajtantrik Dal in 2013.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n               ', 'A court in Sylhet on Monday ordered to send the former acting vice-president of the district unit of Bangladesh Chhatra League, Hiran Mahmud Nipu, to jail in the case for attacking on a joint-rally of Communist Party of Bangladesh and Bangladesh Samajtantrik Dal in 2013.\r\n\r\nActivists of BCL, student organisation of ruling Awami League, led by Nipu had attacked the rally at Court Point in the city on September 15, 2013, that injured at least 15 people including the CPB president Muzahidul Islam Selim.\r\n\r\nShah Paran police arrested Nipu from Baluchar area in the city at around 10-45pm on Sunday, the police said. \r\n\r\nOn Monday noon, the police produced the BCL leader to the Sylhet metropolitan chief magistrate court after showing him arrested in the case and sought the courtâ€™s directive in this regard.\r\n\r\nWhen contacted, Shah Paran police officer-in-charge Shahjalal Munshi told that the chief metropolitan magistrate Saifuzzaman Hero ordered to send Nipu to jail in the case.\r\n\r\nMentioning there were more allegations against Nipu, the police officer said the BCL leader has recently threatened to kill the Education Engineering Departmentâ€™s divisional executive engineer Nazrul Hakim to kill as a bid to get a work of the department.\r\n\r\n               ', '230.jpeg'),
(13, 'SYLHET', 'No election before 2019: Nasim ', 'The health affair minister Mohammad Nasim on Wednesday has said no election would be held in the country before ending the tenure of the present Awami League-led government.\r\n               ', 'The health affair minister Mohammad Nasim on Wednesday has said no election would be held in the country before ending the tenure of the present Awami League-led government.\r\n\r\nStating the country is going ahead in the leadership of prime minister Sheikh Hasina, the health minister said any election before the scheduled time would not be held in the country, despite hatching conspiracies against the government.\r\n\r\nâ€œElection must be held. That would take place in 2019,â€ Nasim said.\r\n\r\nHe was addressing the 4th death anniversary programme of freedom fighter and former Sylhet district AL secretary Iftekhar Hossain Shamim at the Sylhet District Council auditorium in the city as chief guest in the evening.\r\n\r\nTerming Sheikh Hasina as a successful prime minister, Nasim said Sheikh Hasina is taking forward the country ignoring the risk of her life.\r\n\r\nâ€œBut, Bangladesh Nationalist Party and Jamaat-e-Islami want to make unrest the country,â€ the health minister alleged.\r\n\r\nHe claimed that nothing can interrupt the trial process of the war crimes and no place would be left for those who committed crimes against the humanity during the countryâ€™s liberation war in 1971.\r\n\r\nâ€œAll of them who committed crimes against humanity during the War of Independence must be tried in the country,â€ he said.\r\n\r\nThe AL city unit president Badar Uddin Ahmad Kamran chaired the programme that was addressed, among others, by Bangladeshâ€™s former high commissioner to the united Nations AKM Momen, AL central orgenising secretary Misbah Uddin Siraj, the partyâ€™s former district president ANM Shafiqul Haque and district general secretary Shafiqur Rahman Chowdhury.\r\n               ', '228.jpeg'),
(14, 'SYLHET', '25 including 4 cops injured in deed writers-hawkers clash in Sylhet - See more at: http://www.en.syl', 'At least 25 people, including 4 cops, were injured in a clash between hawkers and deed writers of Sylhet land registry office in the city on Tuesday afternoon.\r\n               ', 'At least 25 people, including 4 cops, were injured in a clash between hawkers and deed writers of Sylhet land registry office in the city on Tuesday afternoon.\r\n\r\nArmed Police Battalionâ€™s sub-inspector Faruk Ahmad and Kotwali police constable Ranjan were among the injured police personnel, the police said.\r\n\r\nEyewitnesses said that several deed writers, including Hasnat, Rajan and Eman, asked Mayeen Uddin, owner of a makeshift shop of clothes, to move his shop from the Registry Math, courtyard of the district land registry office, at around 3-45pm.\r\n\r\nThe deed writers locked in exchanging heated words with the makeshift shop owner after he rejected to move from the ground, triggering a clash among the deed writers and the street vendors of the city that injured more than 25, including 4 cops, of both sides, the witnesses said.\r\n\r\nThe city unit of Hawkers League president Abdur Rakib claimed that more than 15 members of their organisation were injured in the clash.  \r\n\r\nWhen contacted, the Kotwali police officer-in-charge Sohel Ahmad confirmed Sylhet View of the news of clash and said they took the situation in control after firing 32 shots in blank.\r\n\r\nâ€œThe police personnel were injured hit by the stones and brick-chips that hurled by the clashers targeting their opposition,â€ the police officer said.\r\n\r\nMentioning the police personnel were admitted at the Police Line Hospital after the incident, the Kotwali OC said that they were preparing to file a case in this connection.\r\n               ', '227.jpeg'),
(15, 'BANGLADESH', '5 dead, 12 rescued as hostage crisis ends', 'At least five bodies were recovered and 12 other injured rescued as a commando team of Bangladesh Army had brought the hostage crisis at Holey Artisan Bakery restaurant in cityâ€™s Gulshan area under control after a 45-minute operation here.\r\n               ', 'At least five bodies were recovered and 12 other injured rescued as a commando team of Bangladesh Army had brought the hostage crisis at Holey Artisan Bakery restaurant in cityâ€™s Gulshan area under control after a 45-minute operation here.\r\n\r\nConfirming the matter, Rapid Action Battalion (RAB) intelligence wing director Lt. Col. Abul Kalam Azad said journalists that the operation has ended.\r\n\r\nThe identity of the deceased could not be identified immediately, he added.\r\n\r\nSome of the injured were taken to the army hospital, he added...\r\n               ', '386.jpeg'),
(16, 'BANGLADESH', '13 hostages rescued alive from Gulshan cafe: PM ', 'Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has said that 13 hostages have been rescued alive from the cafÃ© in Gulshan-2 that was attacked by armed gunmen on Friday night.\r\n               ', 'Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has said that 13 hostages have been rescued alive from the cafÃ© in Gulshan-2 that was attacked by armed gunmen on Friday night.\r\n\r\nThe 12-hour-long hostage crisis at the cafÃ© popular with foreigners ended around 9:30am on Saturday after a two hour long assault by armed forcesâ€™ commandos.\r\n\r\nHasina said that six gunmen have been killed during the raid and one of them was captured alive.\r\n\r\nThat raises possibility of a major intelligence breakthrough into the ongoing radical violence in the country. \r\n               ', '385.jpeg'),
(18, 'BANGLADESH', 'Japan offers Bangladesh help to battle terrorism after hostage crisis.', 'Japan has said it will stand by Bangladesh in its drive to free hostages, including Japanese nationals, taken at a cafe in Dhaka.\r\n               ', 'Japan has said it will stand by Bangladesh in its drive to free hostages, including Japanese nationals, taken at a cafe in Dhaka.\r\n\r\nJapanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, speaking to reporters at his office in Tokyo on Saturday morning local time, termed the incident as â€˜unfortunateâ€™.\r\n\r\nHe also expressed eagerness to provide any kind of help to suppress terrorism.\r\n\r\nAbe said the Japanese embassy in Dhaka was ordered to rescue the Japanese nationals alive from the hostage situation.\r\n\r\nThe Japanese premier said he had also asked the Bangladesh government to take any kind of step to tackle the crisis.\r\n\r\nHe has cancelled his tour to Hokkaido scheduled for Saturday.\r\n\r\nJapanâ€™s Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshihide Suga said his country had received confirmed reports of several Japanese nationals among the hostages in Dhaka.\r\n\r\nHe said a team was sent to Bangladesh to help the Japanese embassy in Dhaka and the government resolve the hostage crisis.\r\n\r\nHe said Japan believed â€˜one of their closest friendsâ€™ Bangladesh would take all sorts of steps to suppress extremists.\r\n \r\nForeign Minister Fumio Kishida also extended sympathy over the incident.\r\n\r\nA total of 906 Japanese nationals are currently in Bangladesh.\r\n               ', '382.jpeg'),
(19, 'BANGLADESH', '2 Police officers killed in Gulshan hostage situation', 'Two police officials were killed and 10 others injured as miscreants charged grenade and opened fire on them in Gulshan diplomatic zone on Friday night.\r\n               ', 'Two police officials were killed and 10 others injured as miscreants charged grenade and opened fire on them in Gulshan diplomatic zone on Friday night.\r\n\r\nThe diseased are Banani police Officer-in-Charge Salauddin and Assistant Commissioner of Detective Branch of Police Rabiul.\r\n\r\nGunmen have stormed a restaurant named Holey Artisan Bakery on Road 79 in the Dhakaâ€™s diplomatic district and taken 30 people at 8pm, Police said.\r\n\r\nAn on-duty police official said that Salahuddin and Rabiul succumbed to their injuries while a few others were left critically injured in the incident.\r\n\r\nPolice has cordoned the restaurant while the injured cops were rushed to adjacent hospitals.\r\n\r\nRAB DG said gunmen took about 30 people hostage inside the restaurant and â€œwe are trying to rescue them carefully.â€\r\n\r\nâ€œWe will negotiate with the terrorists if necessary to bring the situation under control,â€ he added.\r\n\r\nHe also urged the newsmen who reached the spot to be safe while covering the incident as it is a challenge for all of us to handle the situation.\r\n               ', '378.jpeg'),
(20, 'BANGLADESH', 'BCL withdraws demo against DU VC', 'The Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL), student wing of ruling Awami League, has withdrawan their movement against the vice-chancellor (VC) of Dhaka University AAMS Arefin Siddique on Friday night (July 1).\r\n               ', 'The Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL), student wing of ruling Awami League, has withdrawan their movement against the vice-chancellor (VC) of Dhaka University AAMS Arefin Siddique on Friday night (July 1).\r\n\r\nBCL Leaders announced the withdrawal of movement after holding a meeting with the VC at his residence.\r\n\r\nBCL central committee president Saifur Rahman Sohag said they withdrew the movement as the authority has already suspended one person over the publication of a controversial article in the souvenir book, published to mark the 95th founding anniversary of the varsity.\r\n\r\nHe further said their movement was not against the VC.\r\n\r\nBCL central committee general secretary SM Zakir Hussain, DU unit president Abid Al Hasan and general secretary Motahar Hossain Prince were present here.\r\n\r\nEarlier in the day, the DU authority suspended acting registrar Syed Rezaur Rahman who wrote an article in the souvenir book mentioning BNPâ€™s founder Ziaur Rahman as the first president of the country.\r\n               ', '376.jpeg'),
(21, 'SPORTS', 'Fit Mustafizur likely to fly to England for Sussex stint after Eid ', '\r\nIf Mustafizur can join up with the team by Jul 13, he will be able to play at least four matches in the group stage\r\n               ', '   l programme is cleared, he is likely to play his first English county match on Jul 15.  On Friday, Jalal Yunus, Chairman of the Bangladesh Cricket Board Media Committee, said the youngster had applied for visa.  "Our medical team has informed us that his (Mustafizur) rehabilitation went well and he is fine now – he is bowling in the nets.  "He will keep improving in the coming days. If he gets a visa, he will head for England on Jul 12 or 13," Yunus added.  Sussex are hoping to have Mustafizur when they take on Hampshire in their backyard, Hove, on Jul 15.  Forced to wait for Mustafizur for an extended period of time, Sussex have roped in Sri Lanka''s Nuwan Kulasekara as a replacement.  Coach Mark Davis'' men have already played eight matches in the Natwest T20 Blast. They are fourth in the points table with eight points in the South Group.  If Mustafizur can join up with the team by Jul 13, he will be able to play at least four matches in the group stage.  Apart from playing in the T20 tournament, the lanky 20-year-old left-arm seamer will also feature in the Royal London One-Day Cup, in which Sussex will have four matches in hand after Jul 13.  If Sussex advance beyond the group stage, the number of matches will obviously go up.  But if they fail, Mustafizur is likely to return home in the first week of August as Sussex''s l', '373.jpeg'),
(22, 'LIFE STYLE', 'Eat fruits, veggies to feel happy ', ' Eating more fruit and vegetables can substantially increase peopleâ€™s happiness levels later, a new study has claimed.\r\n               ', 'Eating more fruit and vegetables can substantially increase peopleâ€™s happiness levels later, a new study has claimed.\r\n\r\nThe study is one of the first major scientific attempts to explore psychological well-being beyond the traditional finding that fruit and vegetables can reduce risk of cancer and heart attacks, researchers said.\r\n\r\nHappiness benefits were detected for each extra daily portion of fruit and vegetables up to 8 portions per day.\r\n\r\nResearchers found that people who changed from almost no fruit and veg to eight portions of fruit and veg a day would experience an increase in life satisfaction equivalent to moving from unemployment to employment.\r\n\r\nThe well-being improvements occurred within 24 months, researchers said.\r\n\r\nâ€œEating fruit and vegetables apparently boosts our happiness far more quickly than it improves human health,â€ said Andrew Oswald from University of Warwick in the UK.\r\n\r\nâ€œPeopleâ€™s motivation to eat healthy food is weakened by the fact that physical-health benefits, such as protecting against cancer, accrue decades later. However, well-being improvements from increased consumption of fruit and vegetables are closer to immediate,â€ said Mr. Oswald.\r\n\r\nThe study followed more than 12,000 randomly selected people. These subjects kept food diaries and had their psychological well-being measured.\r\n\r\nResearchers found large positive psychological benefits within two years of an improved diet.\r\n\r\nâ€œPerhaps our results will be more effective than traditional messages in convincing people to have a healthy diet,â€ said Redzo Mujcic from University of Queensland in Australia.\r\n\r\nâ€œThere is a psychological payoff now from fruit and vegetables â€” not just a lower health risk decades later,â€ said Mr. Mujcic.\r\n\r\nThe findings were published in the American Journal of Public Health.\r\n\r\nSource: Agencies \r\n               ', '392.jpeg'),
(23, 'SYLHET', '273 Accused of various cases arrested S.Surma in last 3 months', 'SYLHET, MONDAY, 15 AUGUST 2016 :: Law and order situation improve in South Surma. South Surma Thana Police arrested many listed accused and recoverd liquor and other things.\r\n               ', 'On 20th July Police arrested Rassel Mia Son of Abdul Jabbar Upazila Zakiganj from the colony of Jahangir Mia and seize 40 bottle phenncidyl. On 25the July police arrested A. Rahim Son of Late Bulu Mia. He hails from Pilla Kandi Upazila Zakiganj. Police recovered 92 bottle phencidyl.\r\n\r\nOn 2nd August South Surma Police raided the Colony of Mukta Mia and recovered 1582 pieces Yaba, 340 foil Heroin, 220gm Ophim.\r\n\r\nSouth Surma O.C Ataur Rahman lead this operation. On April police arrested 50 warrented accused. They recovered 50 piece Yaba and 29 bottle Phencidyl on May.\r\n\r\nOn May Police arrested 66 warranted accused on June 2016, 78 accused at various charges were arrested. On July they arrested 77 person and recover 35 piece Yaba. Police is alart to arrest yaba king Shahin.\r\n\r\n               ', '583.jpeg'),
(24, 'BANGLADESH', 'SP Babul Aktar resigns ', 'SYLHET, 15TH AUGUST, 2016 :: Home Minister Asaduzzaman Khan Kamal has said Superintendent of Police Babul Aktar has tendered his resignation letter. \r\n               ', 'Kamal told it a  private station Independent TV on Sunday night: â€œThe file from the Police Headquarters includes Babul Aktarâ€™s resignation letter written by him.â€\r\n\r\n\r\nâ€œThe matter is awaiting our decision. We will make the decision soon,â€ he added.\r\n\r\n\r\nInspector General of Police AKM Shahidul Hoque said he had heard Babul â€œis mentally depressed and is not in a state of mind to continue workâ€.\r\n               ', '578.jpeg'),
(25, 'INTERNATIONAL', ' crashes kills atleast 33', '16TH AUGUST, 2016 :: At least 33 people died and 28 others were injured when an overcrowded bus veered off a mountain highway in Nepal .\r\n\r\n               ', '\r\nHome ministry official Chiranjivi confirmed the incident.\r\n\r\nThe bus veered off Arniko highway Monday and rolled about 150 meters (500 feet).\r\n\r\nParts of the bus, bodies and luggage were scattered on the forested slopes below the highway.\r\n\r\nBus crashes are generally blamed on poorly maintained roads and vehicles in Nepal.', '584.jpeg'),
(26, 'INTERNATIONAL', '70 dead as blast hits Pakistan hospital ', 'SYLHET,8TH AUGUST,2016 :: A bomb blast has killed  atleast 70 people at a hospital in the city of Quetta in south-west Pakistan, police say. ', 'Many others were injured in  the attack, which happened at the entrance to the emergency department where the body of a prominent lawyer  Bilal Anwar Kasi shot dead earlier on Monday was being brought.\r\n\r\nBomb Disposal Squad officials confirmed the explosion was a suicide bombing. It was not clear who the attackers were.There was no claim of responsibility for the blast.\r\n\r\nCondemning the attack, Balochistan Chief Minister Sanaullah Zehri told that Indian intelligence agency Research and Analysis Wing (RAW) was behind terror incidents in Quetta.\r\n\r\nPakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif condemned the attacks. "No-one will be allowed to disturb the peace of the province," he said. \r\n               ', '558.jpeg'),
(27, 'SPORTS', 'Siddikur goes into action in Rio Olympics Today', 'SYLHET,11th AUGUST,2016 :: Bangladesh ace golfer Siddikur Rahman will make his debut in the 31st Olympic Games in Rio today taking part in the menâ€™s individual stroke play. \r\n               ', 'On Monday, Bangladeshi ace shooter and the 2014 Commonwealth Games silver medalist Abdullah Hel Baki was eliminated from the qualification round of his favourite Olympics event, menâ€™s 10-metre air rifles, at the Olympic Shooting Centre in Rio.\r\n\r\nBaki finished 25th among the 50 competitors scoring 621.2 in six qualifying series. \r\n               ', '572.jpeg'),
(28, 'LIFE STYLE', '17 foods that make you radiant', 'The festive season is over and so should be the over-indulging in sweets, fried food and snacks. This is the perfect time to recharge your body and detoxify it. Here are a few super foods that can help...\r\n               ', 'Eggs\r\nWith their rich protein, vitamin and mineral content, eggs contribute significantly to improving your concentration, maintaining healthy weight, developing the brain, strengthening eyesight, clotting the blood as well as preventing both birth defects and breast cancer says nutritionist Pooja Makhija.\r\n\r\nQuinoa\r\nThis resembles couscous when boiled and can be used as a substitute for rice. Like egg, Quinoa is a 100% reference protein which has all nine essential amino acids, including lysine, which no other cereal has, states Pooja.\r\n\r\nBlueberries\r\nBlueberries has the highest antioxidant content of all fresh fruit and is rich in Vitamins A, B Complex, C and E as well as in anthocyanin, copper, selenium, zinc and iron say experts. It is one of the best sources of antioxidants in the world has been known to fight super battles against disease, ageing, heart ailments and belly fat.\r\n\r\nPumpkin\r\nBoth the seeds and the flesh of this Super food are bursting with benefits. The fruit itself is high in antioxidants, Vitamins A, C, K and E and is a rich source of magnesium, potassium and iron. Pumpkin seeds have been associated with treating osteoporosis, prostate problems, depression and preventing cancer. ', '337.jpeg'),
(29, 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'Annoying Facebook Posts', 'MARUF KHAN MUNNA,SYLHET, 11th AUGUST,2016 :: Facebook, twitter, Instagram etc. are the popular social networking site.Among them Facebook is the most famous which is filled with great facebook pages and also dumb ones. Most of the pages is posting spamming news feed, annoying types status  these days.\r\n               ', 'To become a genious you close your book and study on facebook! Because most of the facebook pages admins  post a pic of a logical reasoning or aptitude problem and add a text â€œOnly for geniusâ€ and youâ€™re good to go.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe all like to complain about annoying people on Facebook -- there are so many of them, after all. Less popular is reflecting on whether you are sometimes that annoying person yourself. But the truth is, even the best people sometimes do some really annoying things on social media.\r\n               ', '569.jpeg'),
(30, 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'Grand finale of â€˜Banglar Gaanâ€™ July 22', 'SYLHET, TUESDAY, 19 JULY, 2016:: The grand finale of â€˜Aarong Dairy Channel i Bangle Gaanâ€™, which has been considered to be the biggest reality show of folk music in the country, will be held on July 22.\r\n               ', 'The mega festival will take place in the Shaheed Suhrawardy National Indoor Stadium in the capital. The best seven contestants, who have been selected from around 40,000 participants across the country, will fight for the crown in the first edition of the reality show.\r\n\r\nThe champion of the reality show will be awarded with BDT 10,00000, while the first runner up will receive BDT 5,00,000 and the second runner up BDT 3,00,000. In addition, there will also be an array of prizes.\r\n\r\nCelebrated folk singer Momtaz will be the special guest judge in the grand finale alongside two main judges, eminent Rabindra Sangeet singer Rezwana Choudhury Bannya and seasoned musician Ayub.\r\n\r\nTo provide further details about the grand finale of â€˜Aarong Dairy Channel i Banglar Gaanâ€™, a press conference was held yesterday in the Channel i premises. Channel i managing director Faridur Reza Sagar, director of Brac Dairy and Food Enterprise Taufikur Rahman, Rezwana Choudhury Bannya, Ayub Bacchu and top seven contestants were present at the press conference.\r\n\r\n               ', '467.jpeg'),
(31, 'TECH', 'PayPal in Bangladesh â€˜from Augustâ€™ ', 'SYLHET, FRIDAY, 15 JULY 2016::  Popular online money transfer agency PayPal is all set to sign an Moe with state-owned Sonali Bank, clearing the decks for its debut in Bangladesh, authorities have confirmed.\r\n               ', 'Sonali Bank Director-in-charge Md Abdur Rob told on Friday that PayPal had responded with positive indications to a proposal made by the bank to sign an MoU.\r\n\r\nâ€œWe hope the service will start in Bangladesh from next monthâ€, he said.\r\n\r\nPayPal is an e-commerce organization through which money can be transferred through the internet using an electronic bank credit or debit card, PayPal quenches or by using virtual cash from Pay Pal accounts.\r\n\r\nThe government has been trying to introduce the service in Bangladesh since 2011. \r\n               ', '430.jpeg'),
(32, 'TECH', 'Zuckerberg meets US conservatives on reported bias', 'Mark Zuckerberg has met with a group of conservative pundits and media personalities to defend the site against allegations of bias.\r\n               ', '\r\n\r\nThe allegations were reported by technology news website Gizmodo, which did not identify the ex-contractor, Al Jazeera reports on Thursday (May 19).\r\n\r\nâ€˜People who look at Facebookâ€™s trending news think that was an accurate representation of what was trending among Facebook users,â€™ Tim Groeling of University of California told Al Jazeera.\r\n\r\nâ€˜That appears not to have been the case.â€™\r\n\r\nâ€˜In fact there was a great deal of editorial judgment by humans in that process that led different stories being injected and different stories being rejected from that process. \r\n               ', '263.jpeg'),
(33, 'TOURISM', 'Bisnakandi', 'Ihtisham Kabir :: I first heard about Bisnakandi last year on my way to Pantomai, a border village in north Gowainghat Upazila. Md. Foyzul Islam, the local Union Parishad Chairman, was with me. I remarked what a beautiful place Gowainghat was, nestled between the Meghalaya hills and the plains of Sylhet. Foyzul suggested if I wanted to visit beautiful spots in the area I should consider Bisnakandi. \r\n               ', 'Thus it was that one rainy morning that I set out towards Bisnakandi from Sylhet. The road took me through Amborkhana towards the airport. A right turn before the airport led us towards a large bridge over the river Gowain. We crossed the stone-crushing centre of Dhupagol where small  mountains of rocks â€“ all different sizes and colours - lined the road. The road itself was full of gigantic potholes, though whether it was worse than my trip here last year was unclear.\r\n\r\nAt Shalutikor Bazar we made a sharp right and headed towards Hadar Par, the launching point for Bisnakandi. After more jarring potholes, the road became narrow but reasonably well-maintained. The rains had inundated farmland on both sides. On the left, beyond the inundated fields, the clouds collided with the towering Khasi Hills. At one           place â€“ Damari â€“ plants grew out of the water and twisted and turned into themselves, creating unexpected reflections in the water. \r\n               ', '339.jpeg'),
(34, 'TOURISM', 'â€œLalakal: a beauty of Sylhetâ€', 'MARUF KHAN MUNNA,SYLHET, 11th AUGUST,2016 :: The river â€˜Sariâ€™ at Lalakhal is one of the the main tourist attraction of Sylhet division which is is about 45 km away from Sylhet city.', 'This is a wide canal known as Lala Khal & the point near Tamabil Road is known as Sharee Nodi means Sharee River.\r\n\r\nThe river is not much deep.It It is the source of Sylhet Sand . The river originates from Meghalaya, India. This river carries huge amount of sediments and stones from the upstream to Bangladesh. \r\n\r\nThe attraction of this canal is the water, which differs variety of colors blue, green and clear water at different points. In the same canal, you will find blue, green, clear water. No one will believe this without having watch.Lalakhal is a place to visit for those who love natural views and boat riding. \r\n               ', '570.jpeg'),
(35, 'BUSINESS', 'Gold prices hiked again in a week', 'Jewellery in Bangladesh have hiked gold prices again in a week, to â€˜match global prices.â€™', 'Association on Saturday said the decision to hike gold prices by up to Tk 1,225 per bhori (11.664 gm) would be effective from Sunday.\r\n\r\nâ€œThe global prices are going up daily. Hence, we have revised it,â€ the associationâ€™s General Secretary Enamul Haque told.\r\n\r\nHe said they might have to opt for further revision if the upward trend in international gold prices were to persist.\r\n\r\nA week ago, on Jun 18, jewellers hiked gold prices by Tk 1,225 per bhori after several rises and drops in the past one year. \r\n               ', '354.jpeg'),
(36, 'BUSINESS', 'Industries cannot have gas before 2018 : Muhith ', 'Finance Minister AMA Muhith has told investors that industriesâ€™ demand for gas cannot be met before the next two years. \r\n               ', 'Minister was interacting with a delegation of the Foreign Chamber of Commerce and Industries at the secretariat on Thursday.\r\n\r\nHe said a shortage of gas in Bangladesh had forced the shipping of the fuel from other countries as Liquefied Natural Gas or LNG.\r\n\r\nAn LNG terminal, the first of its kind in Bangladesh, is coming up at Moheshkhali.\r\n\r\nIt would be another two years before the terminal became operational, the minister said, urging industries to wait till then.\r\n\r\nThe LNG terminal is scheduled to be completed by 2018.\r\n\r\nOnce operational, it would hold a little over 0.1 million cubic metre of LNG and would be able to offer a daily supply of 500 million cubic feet. \r\n               ', '333.jpeg'),
(37, 'INTERNATIONAL', 'Trump unfit to be president: Obama', 'US President Barack Obama said Republican nominee Donald Trump is unfit to be president.\r\n               ', 'He also questioned why his party still supports the New York billionaire`s candidacy.\r\n\r\nTrump has faced a barrage of criticism in recent days from political allies as well as opponents after he criticized the parents of US army captain Humayun Khan, who was killed in Iraq in 2004.\r\n\r\nMr Obama said he had policy differences with previous Republican presidents and candidates - but added that he had never thought they could not function as president\r\n               ', '469.jpeg'),
(38, 'INTERNATIONAL', 'ISIS Attack at Kabul ,Kills At Least 81,Injured 230', 'Sylhet, 24th July , 2016 :: Afghanistanâ€™s Interior Ministry says at least 81 dead and 230 wounded people were Saturday rushed to a Kabul hospital following a powerful explosion that ripped through a crowd of minority Shiite Hazara protesters.\r\n               ', 'Islamic State has said it was behind the attack on a protest march in the Afghan capital Kabul. The IS-linked Amaq news agency confirmed that and  said two fighters "detonated explosive belts at a gathering of Shia" in Kabul.\r\n\r\nAfghan President Ashraf Ghani said he was â€œdeeply saddenedâ€, adding: â€œPeaceful protest is the right of every citizen, but opportunist terrorists infiltrated the crowds and carried out the attack, killing and injuring a number of citizens including some security forces.â€\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Hazara community, the poorest of Afghanistanâ€™s ethnic groups, accounts for about nine percent of Afghanistanâ€™s population and is the countryâ€™s third-largest minority.', '512.jpeg'),
(39, 'SPORTS', 'BCB arranges Cricket Carnival for school kids', 'SYLHET, MONDAY, 18 JULY 2016:: A countrywide Cricket Carnival 2016 for Under-12 age group by Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) started Friday aiming to create interest among the school-children and awareness among their guardians.\r\n               ', 'BCB is organising the carnival in two phases in association with the National Sports Council (NSC) in 70 separate venues across the country.\r\n\r\nEach venue is scheduled to host seven matches in a day. The format is 12-overs-a-side inside a 30 yard circle.\r\n\r\nA total of 32 children (boys and girls) will be selected from each district or venue based on performance in the first phase. Selected players will undergo a seven-day basic training programme for the second phase.\r\n\r\nThe carnival was held in 33 district venues on the first day. It will take place at five separate venues in capital Dhaka on July 18 and 19, followed by a further 32 district venues on July 22 to complete the first phase.\r\n', '456.jpeg'),
(43, 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'Taylor Swift World''s Highest Earning Celebrity', 'SYLHET, FRIDAY, 15 JULY, 2016:: Taylor Swift has become the world''s highest paid celebrity after raking in $170m (Â£131m) last year. \r\n               ', 'The pop star''s huge earnings put her ahead of fellow chart-toppers Adele at number nine on the Forbes list with $80.5m, Madonna at 12 with $76.5m, Rihanna at 13 with $75m and Katy Perry at 63 with $41m.\r\n\r\nThe Shake It Off singer''s 1989 World Tour earned more than $200m last year.\r\n\r\nOne Direction came second after earning $110m which should tide them over while they enjoy a hiatus from making music.\r\n\r\nHarry Styles is currently filming Christopher Nolan''s new film Dunkirk, while bandmates Louis Tomlinson, Niall Horan and Liam Payne are rumoured to be working on new music.\r\n\r\n               ', 'swift.jpeg'),
(44, 'TECH', 'Google Glass goes dark on its social media accounts ', 'Four years after unveiling its wearable glass headset, Alphabet Inc''s Google shut down several social media accounts linked to the Glass gadget, ending its push to popularise the pricey eyeglasses with consumers.\r\n               ', 'On Tuesday, Twitter, Facebook and Instagram accounts for Google Glass were no longer active, a development first reported on the website 9to5Google.\r\n \r\nA statement on the Google Plus page said: "Hi Explorers, weâ€™ve had a blast hanging out with you on G+ throughout the Explorer Program." It went on to instruct users to get in touch with questions on the support page for Glass.\r\n \r\nThe company declined to comment on the decision.\r\n \r\nGoogle stopped selling Glass to consumers last year noting that it was time for a strategy reset, and the head of the Google X research lab has since then said that the hype surrounding the $1,500 device became overblown considering it was merely a prototype and not a finished product.\r\n \r\nGlass was greeted with enthusiasm among tech aficionados when it was first unveiled in 2012. But the device, which allows users to access e-mail messages on its eye-level screen and to record video with a tiny camera, quickly ran into problems.\r\n               ', '213.jpeg'),
(45, 'LIFE STYLE', 'Homemade Hair Conditioner Recipe', 'conditioner is an essential step in any hair-care routine. Conditioning helps the hair retain moisture, smooths hair cuticles and also helps keep the hair shiny and lustrous.\r\n               ', '\r\nHoney hair conditioner\r\n\r\nIngredients\r\n3 tbsp honey\r\n6 tbsp coconut oil\r\n\r\nInstructions\r\nStir together the honey and coconut oil and apply this on your hair. Cover your hair with a shower cap and allow it to stay on for about 30 minutes. This will allow the honey  to melt and spread to all your strands, thereby nourishing them better. Shampoo and rinse your hair thoroughly after this.\r\n\r\n\r\nEgg conditioner\r\n\r\nIngredients\r\n1 egg\r\n2 tbsp olive oil\r\n2 tbsp honey\r\n\r\nInstructions\r\nMix together the egg, olive oil and honey and apply it on your hair. Now cover your hair with a shower cap and leave it on for about 30 minutes. Once youâ€™re done, rinse the conditioner off with cool water.\r\n\r\nMilk and banana conditioner\r\n\r\nIngredients\r\n1 cup of milk\r\n1 banana\r\n1 tsp coconut oil\r\n\r\nInstruction\r\nMix the banana and milk to make a smooth paste. Add the coconut oil to this mixture and blend this well. Now, wet your hair with some lukewarm water and apply this paste on your hair. After this, cover your hair with a shower cap and leave it on for 30 minutes. Rinse if off with cold water when youâ€™re done', '287.jpeg'),
(46, 'TOURISM', 'Now, play chess on Facebook Messenger!', 'To play chess on the Facebook Messenger, all you need to do is enter "@fbchess play" to begin playing a game with the person you''re chatting with, cent.com reported on Wednesday. \r\n               ', 'To move your pieces, you''ll need to be familiar with the commands used to refer both the pieces and locations on the board. Entering a command such as "@fbchess Pd3" would move a pawn to the corresponding location.\r\n\r\nA cheat sheet of piece names was provided by BetaNews: K is for king, Q for queen, B for bishop, N for knight, R for rook and P is for pawn.\r\n               ', '214.jpeg'),
(47, 'BUSINESS', 'Industries cannot have gas before 2018 : Muhith ', 'Finance Minister AMA Muhith has told investors that industriesâ€™ demand for gas cannot be met before the next two years.\r\n               ', 'The minister was interacting with a delegation of the Foreign Chamber of Commerce and Industries at the secretariat on Thursday.\r\n\r\nHe said a shortage of gas in Bangladesh had forced the shipping of the fuel from other countries as Liquefied Natural Gas or LNG.\r\n\r\nAn LNG terminal, the first of its kind in Bangladesh, is coming up at Moheshkhali.\r\n\r\nIt would be another two years before the terminal became operational, the minister said, urging industries to wait till then.\r\n\r\nThe LNG terminal is scheduled to be completed by 2018.\r\n\r\nOnce operational, it would hold a little over 0.1 million cubic metre of LNG and would be able to offer a daily supply of 500 million cubic feet.\r\n               ', '333.jpeg'),
(48, 'SPORTS', 'Terry will remain Chelsea''s captain: Conte ', '\r\nLong-serving defender John Terry will remain Chelsea''s captain in the coming season, new manager Antonio Conte said on Thursday at his first news conference since joining the Premier League club.', 'Long-serving defender John Terry will remain Chelsea''s captain in the coming season, new manager Antonio Conte said on Thursday at his first news conference since joining the Premier League club.\r\n\r\nTerry, 35, signed a new one-year contract at Stamford Bridge in May to end speculation that he was going to leave the London club after more than 700 appearances. He remains a firm favourite with the club''s fans.\r\n\r\n"John Terry is captain of this team. He is a great player with a great personality and charisma. He knows the club. We take all decisions together with the club and I am very happy John signed," Conte said.\r\n\r\nConte, who guided Juventus to three successive Serie A titles from 2012 to 2014 before becoming the Italian national team coach, has replaced interim manager Guus Hiddink.\r\n\r\nKnown for his motivational powers and fiery touchline presence, the Italian said the team would need to emulate his work ethic to get back to winning ways after missing out on qualification for European football.\r\n\r\n"Every manager has his own idea of football and I want to transfer my ideas to the players. I have great passion for football, for my team and my work," he added.\r\n\r\n"It''s important to have players who are ready to fight, play good football and transfer our passion and emotion to the fans. I am a worker. I suffer during the game. I want my players and the fans to see this."\r\n\r\nChelsea, the 2014-15 Premier League champions, finished only 10th in the table last season and parted company with manager Jose Mourinho midway through the campaign.\r\n\r\n"Last season was a bad season," Conte said. "We must fight for the title, we belong in the Champions League and we must stay there."\r\n\r\n"This league is very difficult. There are six or seven teams that can win the title. This situation excites me."\r\n\r\nConte is the fifth Italian to manage Chelsea, following in the footsteps of Gianluca Vialli, Claudio Ranieri, Carlo Ancelotti and Roberto Di Matteo.', '426.jpeg'),
(49, 'SPORTS', 'Rahat, Yasir push Pakistan closer ', 'Sylhet,17th July,2016:: Three wickets from Rahat Ali before lunch and two more in the afternoon for Yasir Shah put Pakistan on course for victory in the Lord''s Test. \r\n               ', 'Sylhet,17th July,2016:: Three wickets from Rahat Ali before lunch and two more in the afternoon for Yasir Shah put Pakistan on course for victory in the Lord''s Test. Set 283 to win after dismissing Pakistan inside the first ten minutes of the morning session, England''s batsmen struggled to build partnerships against a constantly probing attack.\r\n\r\nShort Scorecard:\r\nPakistan 339 and 215 (Shafiq 49, Sarfraz 45, Woakes 5-32)\r\nEngland 272 and 155 for 6 (Bairstow 28*, Woakes 5*) need a further 128 runs to beat. \r\n               ', '451.jpeg'),
(50, 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'Sridevi to receive outstanding achievement award', 'Bollywood diva Sridevi will be felicitated for her outstanding achievement in Indian cinema at the upcoming 17th IIFA Awards, reports The Indian Express.\r\n               ', 'The 52-year-old actress, who has worked in Tamil, Hindi, Telugu, Malayalam and Kannada films, made her Bollywood debut as a child artist with the 1975 movie â€œJulieâ€.\r\n\r\nIn her career spanning over 40 years, the actress has given various memorable performances in film like â€œSadma,â€ â€œMr Indiaâ€, â€œLamheâ€, â€œChandniâ€, â€œChaalbaazâ€, â€œKhuda Gawahâ€ and â€œEnglish Vinglishâ€.\r\n\r\nStalwarts of Indian cinema like VK Murthy, Rekha, and Yash Johar have previously been recipients of this award.\r\n\r\nThe award will be presented to the actress at the main ceremony, held during the four-day long â€˜IIFA Weekendâ€™ from June 23-26 2016 in Madrid, Spain.\r\n               ', '297.jpeg'),
(51, 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'Heard in marriage split', 'Film star Johnny Depp and his actress wife Amber Heard are to divorce, US court documents have revealed.\r\n               ', 'Johnny Depp and his actress wife Amber Heard are to divorce, US court documents have revealed.\r\n\r\nHeard, 30, filed for divorce in Los Angeles Superior Court citing irreconcilable differences, reports the BBC.\r\n\r\nThey married 15 months ago and have no children.\r\n\r\nThey have recently been embroiled in a legal case in Australia after Heard took two dogs into the country illegally. She pleaded guilty in April to a charge of falsifying documents.\r\n\r\nDepp, 52, and Heard met while co-starring in the 2011 film The Rum Diary.\r\n\r\nIn the court papers, Texan-born Heard listed the separation date as Sunday.\r\n\r\nCelebrity news website TMZ reported that Depp had asked a judge to reject Heard''s claim for spousal support.\r\n\r\nThe split comes days after the death of Deppâ€™s mother. His latest film, Alice Through the Looking Glass, is due to be released on Friday.\r\n\r\nThe Australian court case started last year when Heard brought two dogs into the country where her husband was filming the latest movie in the Pirates of the Caribbean series.\r\n\r\nWhen the case was settled, the couple released a video apology expressing remorse and advising travelers to respect Australian quarantine laws.\r\n\r\nHowever, Australiaâ€™s Deputy PM Barnaby Joyce had threatened to have the dogs put down, triggering a war of words with Depp that lasted for months.\r\n\r\nThe actor recently said on a US TV show that Joyce looks â€˜somehow inbred with a tomatoâ€™.\r\n\r\nJoyce responded by saying he was â€˜pulling stringsâ€™ in Johnny Deppâ€™s head, like film villain Hannibal Lecter. \r\n               ', '288.jpeg'),
(52, 'LIFE STYLE', '7 beauty Benefits of Neem', 'Neem is often ignored by urban folks in favor of more synthetic ingredients, but it has been used in Ayurveda for over 4,000 years.\r\n               ', '\r\n\r\n\r\nPurifying water\r\nBoil a concoction of neem leaves (about 50 leaves in two litres of water) till the leaves are soft and discoloured, and the water turns green. Strain and store in a bottle. Add about 100 ml of this to your bath water to rid the skin of infections, acne and whiteheads.\r\n\r\nSkin toner\r\nThis can also be used as a skin toner â€” just dip a cotton ball into the liquid and wipe your face with it every night. This will clear acne, scars, pigmentation and blackheads. This potion can be used as a hair rinse to treat dandruff and excessive hairfall.\r\n\r\nFace pack\r\nCut about 10 neem leaves and boil them with small segments of orange peel in a little water. Pound them to a pulp. Add a little honey, yoghurt and soy milk, to form a smooth paste. Apply this to your face (can be done thrice a week). This will clear acne and breakouts, dry up whiteheads, pull out blackheads and even reduce the appearance of pores. Honey and neem are excellent moisturisers.\r\n\r\nHair conditioner\r\nA paste made of neem leaves boiled in water and honey, and applied to the hair, leaves it well-conditioned, without frizz and dandruff free.\r\n\r\nHealer\r\nExtracts of neem leaves and seeds produce pain-relieving, anti-inflammatory and fever-reducing compounds that can aid in the healing of cuts, burns, ear aches, sprains and headaches.\r\n\r\nRoot cure\r\nThe bark and roots of the neem tree have medicinal properties; in powdered form, they can be used to control lice and dandruff. Neem has anti-bacterial properties that help fight against skin infections such as acne, psoriasis, scabies and eczema among others.\r\n\r\nPour oil on it\r\nNeem oil, leaves and neem extracts are used to manufacture health and beauty care products. Some products that use neem include soaps, bath powders, shampoos, lotions and creams, toothpastes and neem leaf capsules. They can be used to increase immunity, as a skin purifier or even as insect repellents, and pet care products. \r\n               ', '338.jpeg');
